pageContext.claim: “And we went down less than any other country, think of that.”
pageContext.analysis: Numerous countries did better economically in the second quarter than the United States after the pandemic struck. The USA suffered a decline of 9.5 percent, which was worse than China (+3.2%), Taiwan (-0.6%), South Korea (-3.0%), Finland (-5.2%), Norway (-5.3%), Indonesia (-5.4%) and others.
